<exercise>
  <title>C4 - Homogeneous second-order linear IVP (ver. 16)</title>
  <statement>
    <p>Find the solution to the given IVP.</p>
    <me>y''-4y'+3y = 0 \hspace{1em} y(0) = -1 , y'(0) = -11</me>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>y= -5 \, e^{\left(3 \, t\right)} + 4 \, e^{t}</me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
